parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The expansion of the plastic fuel tank can cause the tank to deform, leading to fuel leakage, fire hazards, and compromised vehicle safety. The distorted tank can also interfere with handlebar movement, ignition switch operation, and tank latch mechanism, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The fuel tank is expanding or swelling
the tank no longer sits correctly on the frame
the handlebars hit the tank or nearly hit it on turning
the tank presses against the ignition switch
the rubber mounts no longer sit on the frame
the tank latch mechanism is affected
and cosmetic damage (ripples) appears on the side of the tank.
